comment_text: I never wanted for my fiancee to ever feel alone. From the first night we hooked off, she cling to my left arm. It was a full moon or close to one because I could still make out her angelic face and that smile that had always brought her many compliments. In my own self afflicted loneliness my heart found a home in here. A UCLA heart specialist had just left after talking to us and asking for our input as he was just getting cought up. 30;min maybe passed. I was by her in her hospital bed when the alarms when off. Dr comes check the monitors only to tell us that her heart could not keep pumping any more. I met her almost 9 yrs ago. Every weekend I would travel for 1-1/2 hrs to spent Friday, Saturday and Sunday with her. Our hearts separated at 9:05am Sunday December 26, 2021. Her name was Crystal, she had Friedreich's Ataxia for 2/3 of her life here on earth. And to say she was special just falls short to describe her. She was came here to rescue my soul.
